social_posts.post_text: Grateful for you guys. 🖤 Thanks to everybody who supports me. In 2023, I’m releasing a new song every month. Get ready.

“Thankful for the Pain” is out everywhere now! Link in bio to hear the full song. 

I wrote this about the people that come into your life for a season or two, bringing an intense connection & impact, but sooner or later you realize they’re more of a lesson disguised as love or friendship. Without pain, we wouldn’t evolve or change as rapidly, so I always strive to remain thankful for the good, the bad, and the in between. 

Comment with your favorite lyric if you’re a real one. 😘

Written, co-produced, & performed by Tyler Shamy
Co-produced, mixed, & mastered by @rokman_official 
Artwork by @suedebrandingco

“You and me are not the same. You wreck havoc on my brain. But I know I’m gonna be okay so I say I’m thankful for the pain. This don’t have to be in vain. LA needs a little rain. Know you’re gonna be okay. Hope you say you’re thankful for the pain”. 

📸: @arod_shoots

This aired years ago, but I realized I never posted this scene featuring a song I wrote with @lancewconrad for The Baker and the Beauty on ABC. The show’s writers provided most of the lyrics & it was our job to make a catchy song out of them. I’m not even close to fluent in Spanish 😆 but I remembered enough pronunciation from high school Spanish to get the job done lol. This was supposed to be a scratch reference vocal & the actor was going to replace my vocal, but they ended up keeping mine. I recorded it in a hotel room in Switzerland on my laptop’s crappy built in microphone, but Lance made it work! Now I never go anywhere without my pro mic lol. This song continues to be one of my most played on Spotify. 😆Hope you enjoy. 🎂😋

@syncstories 🙏🏼🖤

Waves by @bigtimerush is out!! 🌊 Had the best time co-writing it with @loganhenderson, @kendallschmidt, & @willventres. Working with BTR in the studio was a dream come true. The guys are insanely talented, dedicated, grounded, genuine, & hilarious. 

Fun fact: @jamesmaslow & I became friends at the callbacks for Big Time Rush 15 years ago. Obviously I didn’t get cast 😆 but it’s felt like such a full circle moment getting to work with them now. 

Thanks to @bigtimerush for taking a chance on me & @willventres for involving me. Mad love & respect for you homies. 🙏🏼💙

How The Good Go Bad is out!! This is easily one of my favorite songs I’ve ever released. I wrote this from the perspective of someone who’s innately good hearted as most people are, but has been so beaten down by life that they go numb or snap, leading them to the dark side. Most villains aren’t born villains. Link in bio. Hope you love it. 💜
